The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, December 15, 2003 				 Microsoft unveils solutions for small units
 A STAFF REPORTER				 Small is beautiful 																								Calcutta, Dec. 14: Microsoft has launched a range of products to cater to the specific requirements of the small and medium business sector.																								The key challenge faced by small and medium businesses is maintaining seamless communication with customers, employees and business processes, managerbusiness development Punit Vanvaria said.																								Small Business Server 2003 and Office Systems Small Business Edition 2003 have incorporated new features that will help businesses address issues specific to the sector, he added.																								Small Business Server 2003 is a fully integrated server that is optimised to help small businesses protect their data, increase productivity and extend their customer reach while reducing complexity and saving administration time.																								Microsoft Office Small Business Edition 2003 provides small businesses with new and improved tools to manage customers and prospects, run marketing campaigns and communicate more effectively which will result in lowering of marketing costs and increased responsiveness to customers.																								The small and medium business segment is clearly the growth engine for our business, said Vanvaria. 																								We strive to build a global small and medium business ecosystem which offers best value to customers. We have always focussed on investing in a strong channel community, which is the best medium to reach out to small businesses, he added.																								The small and medium business segment contributes to 50 per cent of the companys earnings in the country. 																								Microsoft currently has a 3000-strong channel base with a presence in 70 cities and is trying to extend the reach of these channel partners.
